  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "paragraph_name": "ERROR-LOG-RECORD",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data structure defines the format for error log records. It contains fields to capture the date and time of the error (ERR-DATE, ERR-TIME), the application and program where the error occurred (ERR-APPLICATION, ERR-PROGRAM), and the location within the program (ERR-LOCATION). It also includes fields to categorize the severity and source of the error, using ERR-LEVEL and ERR-SUBSYSTEM respectively. The ERR-LEVEL field uses 88-level condition names to define possible values such as 'L' for Log, 'I' for Info, 'W' for Warning, and 'C' for Critical. Similarly, ERR-SUBSYSTEM uses 88-level condition names to define the subsystem where the error originated, such as 'A' for Application, 'C' for CICS, 'I' for IMS, 'D' for DB2, 'M' for MQ, and 'F' for File. The structure also includes two error code fields (ERR-CODE-1, ERR-CODE-2), a message field (ERR-MESSAGE), and an event key field (ERR-EVENT-KEY) for identifying specific events. This record is intended to be used for consistent and structured error logging across different applications and subsystems.",
